1
00:00:21,890 --> 00:00:26,370
(X Theater)

2
00:01:44,910 --> 00:01:46,750
We'll start eating when Mom gets back.

3
00:01:46,750 --> 00:01:47,630
Okay?

4
00:01:47,630 --> 00:01:48,550
Okay.

5
00:01:50,910 --> 00:01:51,750
You're back.

6
00:01:53,990 --> 00:01:54,990
It smells so good.

7
00:01:55,470 --> 00:01:56,630
What did you make?

8
00:01:57,060 --> 00:01:58,910
Mengmeng, I'm home.

9
00:01:59,470 --> 00:02:00,910
Mom, come.

10
00:02:02,700 --> 00:02:04,830
You even had time to do hot pot today?

11
00:02:04,830 --> 00:02:06,420
The tattoo store closed early today.

12
00:02:08,900 --> 00:02:10,270
You don't look good; what's wrong?

13
00:02:11,700 --> 00:02:13,110
My stomach's been hurting.

14
00:02:13,900 --> 00:02:15,270
Why not go get it checked?

15
00:02:15,830 --> 00:02:18,270
No need.
I've gotten medicine from the clinic.

16
00:02:18,270 --> 00:02:19,180
Don't worry.

17
00:02:21,540 --> 00:02:26,340
=Persona=
=Episode 8=

18
00:02:27,460 --> 00:02:29,070
You can't go abroad

19
00:02:29,070 --> 00:02:30,450
without any connections in Pingtan,

20
00:02:30,620 --> 00:02:32,460
especially with your background.

21
00:02:35,180 --> 00:02:36,420
This guy's name is Feichuan.

22
00:02:36,670 --> 00:02:37,860
Call him.

23
00:02:37,860 --> 00:02:39,110
He can send you abroad.

24
00:02:39,110 --> 00:02:41,500
(Feichuan)

25
00:02:45,420 --> 00:02:47,020
How did you know someone like him?

26
00:02:50,110 --> 00:02:51,550
Back then, Mengmeng's grandma

27
00:02:51,550 --> 00:02:53,550
told me her son died at sea
while fishing.

28
00:02:54,230 --> 00:02:56,140
She asked me to leave with Mengmeng.

29
00:02:57,420 --> 00:02:59,550
It was so sudden for me to believe it.

30
00:03:00,550 --> 00:03:01,860
I went around asking everyone.

31
00:03:02,420 --> 00:03:03,550
Only then did I learn

32
00:03:04,950 --> 00:03:06,420
that he went abroad

33
00:03:06,700 --> 00:03:08,230
on Feichuan's ship.

34
00:03:14,020 --> 00:03:15,830
That family knew you were kind

35
00:03:15,830 --> 00:03:17,420
and took advantage of you.

36
00:03:22,420 --> 00:03:24,550
Later, someone spotted him abroad.

37
00:03:25,420 --> 00:03:27,700
He thought life overseas
would be better.

38
00:03:28,420 --> 00:03:30,110
But things turned out just the same.

39
00:03:31,390 --> 00:03:33,110
At the time,
I couldn't believe it at all.

40
00:03:33,420 --> 00:03:34,990
So, I went to Feichuan again,

41
00:03:35,300 --> 00:03:36,990
asking him over and over for answers.

42
00:03:37,300 --> 00:03:38,830
He got annoyed

43
00:03:39,430 --> 00:03:40,270
and asked me,

44
00:03:40,270 --> 00:03:41,790
"Can't you live without that man?"

45
00:03:42,860 --> 00:03:43,990
Those words

46
00:03:44,420 --> 00:03:45,700
broke my last bit of hope.

47
00:03:47,670 --> 00:03:49,230
Just when I was about to leave,

48
00:03:49,830 --> 00:03:51,830
someone showed up
to mess with his business.

49
00:03:52,020 --> 00:03:54,020
I shouted, "Police!"

50
00:03:54,270 --> 00:03:55,670
and scared the group off.

51
00:03:55,860 --> 00:03:57,860
He thought he owed me for that

52
00:03:58,270 --> 00:04:00,270
and told me if I needed something,

53
00:04:00,270 --> 00:04:01,270
he'd make sure to help.

54
00:04:12,580 --> 00:04:14,270
I appreciate the offer,

55
00:04:15,270 --> 00:04:16,550
but I can't make that call.

56
00:04:20,710 --> 00:04:22,110
You don't believe me, do you?

57
00:04:22,110 --> 00:04:22,990
Of course, I do.

58
00:04:22,990 --> 00:04:23,990
I believe you.

59
00:04:28,110 --> 00:04:29,710
I've felt terrible enough

60
00:04:29,710 --> 00:04:30,990
about dragging Danshun into this.

61
00:04:32,110 --> 00:04:34,110
It doesn't concern you anyway.

62
00:04:34,990 --> 00:04:35,860
You have Mengmeng.

63
00:04:35,860 --> 00:04:37,260
You have your own life.

64
00:04:39,710 --> 00:04:41,420
I can't drag you into this.

65
00:04:44,670 --> 00:04:45,510
Hong,

66
00:04:46,470 --> 00:04:49,030
helping you is helping myself.

67
00:04:50,030 --> 00:04:51,790
If you leave safely,

68
00:04:51,790 --> 00:04:53,590
Danshun and I can also leave this place.

69
00:04:54,420 --> 00:04:55,590
You two are leaving, too?

70
00:04:57,990 --> 00:04:59,470
I mentioned it to him before,

71
00:04:59,470 --> 00:05:01,150
but he didn't agree at that time.

72
00:05:01,670 --> 00:05:03,030
Now, I finally understand

73
00:05:03,260 --> 00:05:04,350
that he was waiting for you.

74
00:05:14,150 --> 00:05:14,990
Don't worry.

75
00:05:17,670 --> 00:05:19,420
Whether I make it out or not,

76
00:05:20,260 --> 00:05:21,150
or whether...

77
00:05:24,470 --> 00:05:25,350
I swear I'll never

78
00:05:25,350 --> 00:05:26,790
turn you or Danshun in.

79
00:05:27,250 --> 00:05:28,260
I won't say a single word

80
00:05:28,260 --> 00:05:29,670
about you two.

81
00:05:31,910 --> 00:05:33,260
Starting today,

82
00:05:34,470 --> 00:05:35,770
let's just pretend we never met.

83
00:05:40,470 --> 00:05:42,590
Actually, Danshun told me about you.

84
00:05:44,150 --> 00:05:46,150
If I had that kind of nerve and courage,

85
00:05:48,030 --> 00:05:49,590
I wouldn't have ended up like this.

86
00:05:52,990 --> 00:05:54,350
What do you mean?

87
00:05:57,030 --> 00:05:59,670
I'm in no place to judge Danshun.

88
00:06:01,230 --> 00:06:02,920
I've been hiding something
from him, too.

89
00:06:10,030 --> 00:06:10,910
Five or six years ago,

90
00:06:10,910 --> 00:06:12,470
something happened to me.

91
00:06:14,230 --> 00:06:16,100
I was 22 and had just moved here.

92
00:06:16,100 --> 00:06:17,260
(Jiankanglu Health Technology)

93
00:06:17,260 --> 00:06:18,340
I didn't know anything.

94
00:06:20,230 --> 00:06:22,670
- And I had a kid with me.
- It's raining so hard.

95
00:06:24,350 --> 00:06:25,470
It's just a bit of rain.

96
00:06:26,150 --> 00:06:27,230
You can't handle this?

97
00:06:27,420 --> 00:06:29,260
I only had one thought.

98
00:06:29,260 --> 00:06:30,790
Someone even brought a child.

99
00:06:30,790 --> 00:06:32,260
How are you supposed to work?

100
00:06:32,910 --> 00:06:34,110
I need to survive.

101
00:06:34,110 --> 00:06:34,950
Manager.

102
00:06:34,950 --> 00:06:37,030
My babysitter couldn't make it today,

103
00:06:37,260 --> 00:06:38,470
so I had to bring her.

104
00:06:38,470 --> 00:06:39,790
What about your sales numbers?

105
00:06:39,790 --> 00:06:41,110
Who's handling your work?

106
00:06:42,550 --> 00:06:44,050
There's barely anyone passing by here.

107
00:06:44,050 --> 00:06:45,420
Who's heading to the market next?

108
00:06:45,420 --> 00:06:46,650
Try to bring more people over.

109
00:06:54,470 --> 00:06:56,110
Can you help me watch Mengmeng?

110
00:06:56,110 --> 00:06:56,950
Sure.

111
00:06:57,150 --> 00:06:57,990
Good girl.

112
00:07:13,350 --> 00:07:14,090
Sir,

113
00:07:14,170 --> 00:07:16,350
we're offering free checkups.
Would you like to join?

114
00:07:16,350 --> 00:07:17,490
- No.
- Take a look.

115
00:07:18,150 --> 00:07:18,990
Ma'am.

116
00:07:19,350 --> 00:07:20,670
We're having a checkup event.

117
00:07:20,820 --> 00:07:22,150
You'll get free eggs.

118
00:07:30,260 --> 00:07:31,110
Mr. Ma.

119
00:07:31,910 --> 00:07:32,910
What brings you here?

120
00:07:34,260 --> 00:07:36,230
You've been working hard all day,

121
00:07:36,230 --> 00:07:37,470
but there's still no result.

122
00:07:37,470 --> 00:07:38,820
Then it's all in vain, right?

123
00:07:39,420 --> 00:07:40,770
Do you know where the problem is?

124
00:07:44,790 --> 00:07:45,630
Look over there.

125
00:07:46,260 --> 00:07:47,150
Look at that lady.

126
00:07:47,150 --> 00:07:49,110
She's rushing off
right after buying groceries,

127
00:07:49,150 --> 00:07:51,030
so she's heading home
to cook for her kid.

128
00:07:51,790 --> 00:07:53,420
She'd just ignore you.

129
00:07:54,260 --> 00:07:55,230
Look at the other one.

130
00:07:56,470 --> 00:07:57,790
She checks everything carefully.

131
00:07:57,990 --> 00:07:59,790
She always haggles for everything.

132
00:08:00,260 --> 00:08:02,470
Earning just a few cents
can make her happy.

133
00:08:02,790 --> 00:08:03,910
Go talk to her.

134
00:08:04,260 --> 00:08:05,670
Tell her we're running a promo.

135
00:08:06,030 --> 00:08:07,350
We're giving away eggs for free.

136
00:08:07,420 --> 00:08:08,470
See if she shows up.

137
00:08:09,030 --> 00:08:09,990
As long as she comes,

138
00:08:10,590 --> 00:08:11,810
we won't let her leave easily.

139
00:08:18,790 --> 00:08:19,910
Go on, try again.

140
00:08:19,910 --> 00:08:20,750
Alright.

141
00:08:24,470 --> 00:08:25,310
Ma'am.

142
00:08:25,420 --> 00:08:26,550
We're having a special event.

143
00:08:26,550 --> 00:08:27,940
You can get a free health checkup

144
00:08:27,940 --> 00:08:28,820
and free eggs.

145
00:08:29,620 --> 00:08:30,500
Great.

146
00:08:31,060 --> 00:08:32,500
Let me take you there.

147
00:08:32,740 --> 00:08:33,780
Just follow me.

148
00:08:34,110 --> 00:08:34,950
Alright.

149
00:08:41,110 --> 00:08:43,350
Ladies and gentlemen,

150
00:08:44,230 --> 00:08:46,660
I'm Ma Weicheng, General Distributor

151
00:08:46,660 --> 00:08:49,160
from Jiankanglu

152
00:08:49,160 --> 00:08:50,990
(Citywide Elderly Care Initiative)
in China.

153
00:08:50,990 --> 00:08:52,430
You can call me Ma

154
00:08:52,780 --> 00:08:53,830
or Weicheng.

155
00:08:55,110 --> 00:08:58,540
On behalf of our entire company,

156
00:08:58,540 --> 00:09:01,140
I'd like to welcome you here today.

157
00:09:02,430 --> 00:09:04,660
So, do you know why you're here today?

158
00:09:05,140 --> 00:09:06,260
You're here to relax.

159
00:09:07,020 --> 00:09:08,430
And what are we here for?

160
00:09:08,430 --> 00:09:09,780
We're here to give.

161
00:09:09,780 --> 00:09:10,900
Give what?

162
00:09:10,900 --> 00:09:11,950
Love

163
00:09:11,950 --> 00:09:13,070
and health.

164
00:09:13,070 --> 00:09:14,780
That's what we call a win-win, right?

165
00:09:15,020 --> 00:09:15,860
Good.

166
00:09:20,620 --> 00:09:21,660
First of all,

167
00:09:22,430 --> 00:09:23,500
I want to ask

168
00:09:24,020 --> 00:09:25,540
everyone a question.

169
00:09:26,740 --> 00:09:28,310
You've reached this age.

170
00:09:28,780 --> 00:09:29,660
What is

171
00:09:30,020 --> 00:09:31,070
the most important thing

172
00:09:31,070 --> 00:09:32,780
in your life?

173
00:09:33,140 --> 00:09:34,310
Your children,

174
00:09:34,780 --> 00:09:35,780
your partner,

175
00:09:36,430 --> 00:09:38,190
or the money in your bank account?

176
00:09:38,190 --> 00:09:39,430
Of course, it's money.

177
00:09:39,430 --> 00:09:40,500
Ma'am, what did you say?

178
00:09:41,430 --> 00:09:42,270
Money.

179
00:09:42,430 --> 00:09:43,270
It's money.

180
00:09:43,860 --> 00:09:45,340
Alright, don't laugh.

181
00:09:46,260 --> 00:09:47,660
Let me give you an example.

182
00:09:47,660 --> 00:09:48,540
Let's say

183
00:09:48,540 --> 00:09:49,380
your children...

184
00:09:49,380 --> 00:09:50,540
You have children, right?

185
00:09:50,540 --> 00:09:51,380
Two sons.

186
00:09:51,380 --> 00:09:52,220
That's wonderful.

187
00:09:52,660 --> 00:09:54,780
Let's imagine one day, your children

188
00:09:55,140 --> 00:09:56,430
tell you

189
00:09:56,780 --> 00:09:57,740
they need money

190
00:09:57,740 --> 00:09:58,780
for something urgent.

191
00:09:58,780 --> 00:10:01,780
Will you give them

192
00:10:01,780 --> 00:10:02,620
all your savings?

193
00:10:03,430 --> 00:10:04,270
Yes.

194
00:10:04,740 --> 00:10:06,740
Then money isn't
the most important thing to you.

195
00:10:06,740 --> 00:10:07,860
Were you just fooling me?

196
00:10:10,140 --> 00:10:11,380
Now, let me flip the question.

197
00:10:12,540 --> 00:10:13,660
If one day,

198
00:10:14,540 --> 00:10:15,660
everyone sitting here

199
00:10:16,310 --> 00:10:17,430
grows old,

200
00:10:18,140 --> 00:10:19,020
falls ill,

201
00:10:20,500 --> 00:10:23,260
and needs all of your son

202
00:10:23,660 --> 00:10:26,780
and daughter-in-law's savings
for your treatment.

203
00:10:27,540 --> 00:10:28,540
Do you think

204
00:10:29,070 --> 00:10:30,500
they'd actually do that?

205
00:10:39,900 --> 00:10:40,740
Not necessarily.

206
00:10:42,070 --> 00:10:42,910
You're not sure.

207
00:10:45,860 --> 00:10:46,900
Alright, that's fine.

208
00:10:48,380 --> 00:10:50,620
Let me share a personal story with you.

209
00:10:52,780 --> 00:10:54,660
When I was a kid, I was super naughty.

210
00:10:55,260 --> 00:10:56,660
Such a naughty boy.

211
00:10:57,380 --> 00:10:58,860
When I was nine,

212
00:10:59,020 --> 00:11:00,780
my school was about to kick me out.

213
00:11:01,540 --> 00:11:03,660
My homeroom teacher
called my mom to school

214
00:11:03,660 --> 00:11:04,660
and told my mom

215
00:11:04,660 --> 00:11:06,430
that I didn't study.

216
00:11:06,900 --> 00:11:07,860
Guess what my mom said?

217
00:11:08,260 --> 00:11:10,140
She said that it was

218
00:11:10,140 --> 00:11:12,430
because what they taught
was too easy for me.

219
00:11:13,140 --> 00:11:15,020
That teacher was so mad.

220
00:11:15,900 --> 00:11:17,540
Later, when we got home,
I asked my mom,

221
00:11:18,310 --> 00:11:19,430
"Why did you say that?"

222
00:11:20,020 --> 00:11:20,950
My mom said,

223
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:23,020
"I respect you,"

224
00:11:23,430 --> 00:11:24,430
"care for you,"

225
00:11:24,660 --> 00:11:26,860
"and protect you as you grow up."

226
00:11:28,660 --> 00:11:30,070
I'm deeply grateful to her.

227
00:11:30,950 --> 00:11:33,260
It's because of a mother like her

228
00:11:34,140 --> 00:11:35,860
that I've come this far

229
00:11:35,860 --> 00:11:36,950
without ever losing my way.

230
00:11:37,140 --> 00:11:38,430
Up to this day,

231
00:11:39,190 --> 00:11:40,340
I've started my own business

232
00:11:40,430 --> 00:11:41,640
and learned to stand on my own.

233
00:11:44,430 --> 00:11:46,020
I truly love my mother.

234
00:11:49,860 --> 00:11:51,020
But five years ago,

235
00:11:54,020 --> 00:11:55,020
she was diagnosed

236
00:11:58,020 --> 00:11:59,270
with an advanced stomach cancer.

237
00:12:00,620 --> 00:12:01,660
I didn't know what to do.

238
00:12:01,660 --> 00:12:04,380
I was still working a regular job,

239
00:12:04,380 --> 00:12:05,540
working for someone else,

240
00:12:06,380 --> 00:12:08,540
so I had to use all my salary

241
00:12:08,540 --> 00:12:10,020
and every bit of my savings.

242
00:12:10,620 --> 00:12:12,260
I found the best doctor,

243
00:12:12,660 --> 00:12:14,140
used every connection we had,

244
00:12:14,380 --> 00:12:16,370
and finally got her admitted
to the best hospital

245
00:12:16,540 --> 00:12:17,660
in our province.

246
00:12:21,660 --> 00:12:22,900
And she never came out again.

247
00:12:27,430 --> 00:12:28,740
I watched her

248
00:12:29,260 --> 00:12:30,430
grow thinner and weaker

249
00:12:31,780 --> 00:12:33,020
day after day.

250
00:12:34,660 --> 00:12:36,070
That's when I understood

251
00:12:36,070 --> 00:12:39,070
what it means to be completely drained.

252
00:12:45,540 --> 00:12:47,070
After that, I started thinking.

253
00:12:48,900 --> 00:12:50,380
I asked myself

254
00:12:52,020 --> 00:12:53,380
what I could've done

255
00:12:53,380 --> 00:12:55,260
to change all of this,

256
00:12:56,780 --> 00:12:59,140
and when I should've started

257
00:12:59,140 --> 00:13:01,020
to spare her all the suffering.

258
00:13:02,310 --> 00:13:03,430
Later, I realized

259
00:13:05,620 --> 00:13:07,240
it had to start from the very beginning.

260
00:13:08,140 --> 00:13:11,020
From the very start,
my mom had to be healthy.

261
00:13:11,020 --> 00:13:12,190
She should never fall ill.

262
00:13:12,500 --> 00:13:15,950
She should live a healthy life
from the very start.

263
00:13:16,900 --> 00:13:18,310
So, when I heard

264
00:13:18,310 --> 00:13:19,190
about Jiankanglu,

265
00:13:19,190 --> 00:13:22,260
I put everything I had on it

266
00:13:22,260 --> 00:13:24,430
without hesitation.

267
00:13:25,140 --> 00:13:26,540
I decided to join them.

268
00:13:26,900 --> 00:13:27,740
Why?

269
00:13:27,900 --> 00:13:29,500
Because I wanted others

270
00:13:29,500 --> 00:13:32,860
to never go through the same pain I did.

271
00:13:33,140 --> 00:13:34,070
I wanted

272
00:13:34,070 --> 00:13:35,780
to bring health and happiness

273
00:13:35,780 --> 00:13:38,020
to every parent out there

274
00:13:38,020 --> 00:13:39,020
and

275
00:13:39,740 --> 00:13:42,020
every child who isn't here today.

276
00:13:47,780 --> 00:13:50,020
Now, please close your eyes with me.

277
00:13:52,620 --> 00:13:54,140
Try to picture this.

278
00:13:56,020 --> 00:13:57,260
One day,

279
00:13:58,260 --> 00:13:59,260
when you grew old,

280
00:14:00,310 --> 00:14:01,150
when illness came,

281
00:14:02,500 --> 00:14:03,780
your children

282
00:14:03,780 --> 00:14:04,780
drained every bit

283
00:14:05,310 --> 00:14:07,020
of their savings for you.

284
00:14:08,140 --> 00:14:09,260
At the office,

285
00:14:10,140 --> 00:14:11,430
their boss scolded them.

286
00:14:12,260 --> 00:14:13,260
At home,

287
00:14:13,660 --> 00:14:15,020
their partner complained.

288
00:14:16,070 --> 00:14:17,950
